name: 7-hexadecanone
Reason: The base structure for comparison is hexadecane, which has a melting point of 18.1 degrees Celsius. The presence of a ketone (carbonyl group, C=O) in 7-hexadecanone generally increases the melting point due to the ability to form stronger intermolecular forces such as dipole-dipole interactions. The rough estimation for a ketone group to increase the melting point compared to an alkane can be around +20 degrees Celsius.
